1
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,559
I'm worried about you.

2
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,999
And what about me?
Have you ever worried about me?

3
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,119
Have you ever missed me?

4
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,199
Good morning.

5
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,280
Mr. Narathon.

6
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:06,839
Who are you really?

7
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:10,720
The way she talks
and behaves reminds me of...

8
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,560
Who?

9
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,640
Sarai.

10
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,319
This is Ms. Pat.

11
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:22,639
She is overseeing this event.

12
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:26,000
And this is Kaimook, the owner
of the photographs you wanted to meet.

13
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:30,319
I can hardly believe you're this young.

14
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,639
You're amazing.

15
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:33,399
Nice to meet you.

16
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,400
Likewise.

17
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:38,120
This is Narathon, my son.

18
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:43,759
The apple really
doesn't fall far from the tree.

19
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:46,479
You're just as handsome
and sophisticated as Mr. Phum.

20
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,080
But personality-wise,

21
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:50,600
I'm a very different apple from the tree.

22
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:56,440
You mean you don't like doing business
the way Mr. Phum does?

23
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,800
Something like that.

24
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,920
Shall we begin discussing work?

25
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:06,640
Of course. Then please,
everyone, let's go to the meeting room.

26
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,000
Please.

27
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,960
Your collaborators

28
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,480
seem to all be women.

29
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,999
Okay.

30
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,959
We'll open with a contemporary
dance performance accompanied by music.

31
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:34,359
The story will be
about marine resources being destroyed.

32
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:37,399
The performers
will dress as coral and seaweed.

33
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,600
Ms. Pat.

34
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:41,399
I think that might feel
too much like a stage play.

35
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,439
I want something more direct.

36
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:47,040
But I think it's okay.

37
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:50,080
Why don't we make a short video instead?

38
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:53,559
Let people see
the true beauty of the ocean

39
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,559
and the damaged coral reefs
with their own eyes.

40
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,760
I like something like this.

41
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:03,239
Then I'll volunteer
to film the underwater footage myself.

42
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,720
Excellent.

43
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,680
Mr. Phum, you should be
the one to dive and guide everyone.

44
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:14,679
It's dangerous for him.

45
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,679
Mr. Phum, what about

46
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:19,160
I hire someone to dive instead?

47
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,520
But if Mr. Phum goes himself,

48
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,359
people will see how sincere you are

49
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:29,160
about conserving
and restoring the coral reefs.

50
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,680
Ms. Pakarang is right.

51
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:35,959
If this is really for the public good

52
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,560
and not for some hidden agenda,

53
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,920
then you should go yourself.

54
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,640
Fine.

55
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,120
I'll go myself.

56
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,040
But...

57
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,320
Okay. Fine.

58
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,880
Ms. Pakarang.

59
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,159
You seem a bit sick.

60
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,479
Why don't you go rest
in the meeting room first?

61
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,000
I'll handle this for you.

62
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,760
Thank you.

63
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,240
Alright.

64
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,120
I'll put this in.

65
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,320
Your coffee
deserves something more special.

66
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,520
That's Ms. Pat's voice.

67
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,280
My eye!

68
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,320
Ms. Pat.

69
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,399
Ms. Pat.

70
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,800
Ms. Pat, what happened?

71
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,040
My eye! My eye...

72
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,960
There's nothing there.

73
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:39,839
There was.

74
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,720
When I was making coffee...

75
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:46,240
Then why did you pick your shoe up?

76
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,600
Why did you pick your shoe up?
What were you trying to do?

77
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,120
Ms. Pat, is something wrong?

78
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:06,519
I must not be feeling well.

79
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:10,440
I barely slept last night.
I worked all night.

80
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:14,480
Why don't you sit down and rest?
I can help you.

81
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,799
It's fine.

82
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,280
I think I should just go back to my room.

83
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,879
I'm sorry, Mr. Phum.

84
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,319
I can't continue the meeting today.

85
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:27,239
That's alright. You can go get some rest.

86
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,280
Okay.

87
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,960
Pat.

88
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,040
Pat.

89
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,520
Pat.

90
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,760
What's got you upset?

91
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:22,199
Weren't you supposed to meet
the person who took the photo

92
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,200
of the Black Coral?

93
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,520
Or did they not show up?

94
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:31,040
She did. But I didn't have
a chance to talk to her much.

95
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,640
Something ridiculous happened.

96
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,280
What happened?

97
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,760
Nothing.

98
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,679
I think you should leave for today.

99
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:46,640
Once I get the information
from Kaimook, I'll call you.

100
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:48,520
Kaimook?

101
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,200
Pat,

102
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,720
which Kaimook? What's her last name?

103
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,039
I told you I don't know.

104
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,920
I haven't spoken with her much.

105
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,360
I only know she works at SAVE SEA.

106
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:04,760
SAVE SEA?

107
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,359
Oh, come on.

108
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,879
I thought it was someone else.

109
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,000
Wow.

110
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:12,040
You know her?

111
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,520
More than that.

112
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,879
She's a friend of my younger sister.

113
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,640
She used to have a huge crush on me

114
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:22,160
and chased after me all the time.

115
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:25,360
I never encouraged it, though.
We drifted apart eventually.

116
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,200
Then,

117
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:37,240
you need to get close to her again.

118
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:45,800
You're not even jealous?

119
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:50,919
I know how much you love me.

120
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,399
Why would I be jealous?

121
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,759
You're doing this for our work.

122
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:58,560
But if you actually
fall in love with Kaimook,

123
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,240
I won't forgive you.

124
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,600
Alright then.

125
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:21,680
For our future and our fortune.

126
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:25,960
I'll get the information
from Kaimook myself

127
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,760
and find out where the Black Coral is.

128
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,600
That's more like it.

129
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,760
Do it for our future.

130
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,280
Yeah?

131
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,560
I'll be there right away.

132
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:09,399
I think we should stop here for today.

133
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,400
I've got something to take care of.

134
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,440
If you want to leave early, then go ahead.

135
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:18,160
I can't leave Kaimook here by herself.

136
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,959
Let's wait until Ms. Pat is feeling better

137
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,840
and schedule another meeting later.

138
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,079
That works.

139
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:29,800
I'll have Pakarang
coordinate everything from here on.

140
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:33,440
Alright. Then I'll head back now.

141
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,600
Goodbye.

142
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,400
Mr. Sompong has improved quite a lot.

143
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,120
Can I talk to him?

144
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,840
Of course.

145
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,640
Where is he now?

146
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,840
There he is.

147
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,240
Sir.

148
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,640
Do you remember me?

149
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:34,759
You hid in my car.

150
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:36,320
Do you remember?

151
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,560
I remember.

152
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,520
I remember.

153
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:51,879
You remember?

154
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:52,799
Oh.

155
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,919
Sir.

156
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:54,880
Don't be afraid.

157
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:59,480
Don't be afraid. We won't hurt you.

158
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,640
Where did you find him?

159
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:09,480
At the beach.

160
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,360
The beach...

161
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:14,800
The beach...

162
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,960
You!

163
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,080
You!

164
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,959
- You!
- Calm down.

165
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:38,239
You!

166
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,519
A ghost!

167
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,479
A sea ghost!

168
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,479
No, she's not.

169
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,119
Calm down. It's nothing.

170
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,359
I didn't kill her!

171
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,480
Come here.

172
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,639
Kaimook.

173
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:51,120
Are you okay?

174
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,040
I'm okay.

175
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,399
So that's why

176
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:06,479
you brought Sompong here.

177
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,280
You were hoping he'd recover

178
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:11,640
and tell us the truth about Sarai's death?

179
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,239
Yes.

180
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,159
I've always had a feeling

181
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:18,760
he was connected to what happened somehow.

182
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,280
From everything you've told me

183
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,959
and everything
we've found out about Sarai,

184
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:28,040
it does seem connected.

185
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:34,079
But judging from Sompong's condition,

186
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,840
recovery won't be easy.

187
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:40,400
Kaimook.

188
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,279
How are you feeling?

189
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:45,000
Are you still shaken?

190
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,560
I'm fine.

191
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,440
I'm really sorry.

192
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,600
I shouldn't have brought you here.

193
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:58,160
Because you brought me today,

194
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:02,800
I came up with an idea.

195
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:05,358
Maybe this method

196
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:08,720
will help us find
Sarai's killer much sooner.

197
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:16,800
What method?

198
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:27,960
I'm sorry.

199
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,600
You...

200
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,600
You're so much like...

201
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,160
Like her.

202
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:47,040
Every time I'm near you,
I feel like I'm near her.

203
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,600
Who?

204
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,120
Let's go get something to eat.

205
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:11,200
<i>She must have been very important to you.</i>

206
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,880
<i>Important enough that you could kill me.</i>

207
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:28,960
If you're bored of my restaurant,
why don't we go dancing?

208
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:33,319
I know a new place
packed with handsome guys.

209
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:34,840
I guarantee you'll feel better.

210
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,199
No. I'm not in the mood.

211
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:41,440
I'd rather sit quietly and think.
Maybe I'll come up with something useful.

212
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:45,480
Suit yourself.
I'll go check on my customers.

213
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:57,999
Rung. Look.

214
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,440
At what? I don't want to look at anything.

215
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,439
Oh, but you definitely want to.

216
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:04,560
Your husband's here with his mistress.

217
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:15,239
Pakarang?

218
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:18,039
So what's the plan? Want to go slap her?

219
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:20,399
I'll tell my staff not to interfere.

220
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,320
No.

221
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:23,559
I already fought with her once.

222
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:25,639
She's not some pig
waiting to be slaughtered.

223
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,839
And with Mr. Phum here,

224
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,640
if I walk over and slap her,
I'll be the idiot.

225
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:32,760
So you're just going to
let her get away with it?

226
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,200
Then,

227
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:45,040
let's find something hot
to pour over her face.

228
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:48,160
Consider it done.

229
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,519
- I'll order now.
- Yes, sir.

230
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:02,360
Stir-fried mixed vegetables.

231
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,520
I'm so sorry.

232
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,160
It's nothing.

233
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,599
Do you have any recommendations for soup?

234
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,320
What the hell are you doing?

235
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:43,159
I told you to trip at that table,
not this one, idiot.

236
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,199
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

237
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,599
You're both idiots.

238
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:49,640
You can't even give instructions properly.
Look. It burns.

239
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,520
Get out.

240
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,360
Clean it.

241
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,080
You idiots.

242
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:54,320
You.

243
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:01,160
"The suffering you cause others
will return to you."

244
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:02,920
Have you heard that?

245
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,760
What do you mean?

246
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:11,080
I know everything you're thinking.

247
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:15,320
Let me warn you. Don't do it again.

248
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,400
Next time, you won't get off this easily.

249
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,160
Wait.

250
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:55,320
Am I drunk from wine?

251
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,879
Why did you bring me here?

252
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:46,040
I'd like to make merit.

253
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,520
Can we go make merit for a moment?

254
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,280
- Sure.
- Please.

255
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:25,039
For any bad karma I've done to you,

256
00:25:25,040 --> 00:25:26,919
physically, verbally, mentally,

257
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:29,480
please forgive me, Sarai.

258
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:42,960
So you finally admit it yourself.

259
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:46,600
The person who killed me was you.

260
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:26,519
I'd like to meditate for a moment.

261
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:28,480
Maybe it'll help calm my mind.

262
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,320
Shall we meditate?

263
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:34,320
Yes.

264
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,040
Sarai?

265
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:23,359
Yes.

266
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,440
Sarai.

267
00:27:58,240 --> 00:27:59,400
Sarai.

268
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:05,960
Is that you, Sarai?

269
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,640
Sarai.

270
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:28,560
I don't want merit from someone like you.

271
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,719
She has no pulse.

272
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,480
She's dead, Venerable Sir.

273
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,160
Why did her body turn cold so quickly?

274
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:12,840
Pakarang.

275
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:16,999
Pakarang.

276
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,759
Pakarang, what's wrong?

277
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:20,960
Pakarang.

278
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:22,760
She's dead.

279
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:25,200
She has no pulse.

280
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,519
That's impossible. Pakarang.

281
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:31,879
Please calm yourself.

282
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:35,519
Birth and death are natural.

283
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:37,679
No, she will be fine.

284
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,159
I'll take her to the hospital.

285
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:40,400
Pakarang.

286
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:54,000
Pakarang, you can't die.

287
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:57,640
I'm taking you to the hospital.
Stay with me.

288
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:04,640
You must die.

289
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,760
Sarai!

290
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,360
Thank you so much for the ride.

291
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:43,280
SAIRUNG

292
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,280
Why is she calling?

293
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:49,400
She never calls me.

294
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:52,519
Just answer it.

295
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:54,160
It might be urgent.

296
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:11,880
Which hospital?

297
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:15,400
I'll be right there.

298
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:27,400
Dad was in a car accident.

299
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,320
He's seriously injured.

300
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:33,120
I'm going to the hospital.

301
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,520
I'm going with you.

302
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:51,320
How is he?

303
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,160
He's still inside.

304
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,440
How did it happen?

305
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:04,679
Your father
took that Pakarang out somewhere.

306
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,480
Their car crashed into a ten-wheeler.

307
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,840
Both of them are in critical condition.

308
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:19,079
They're in the doctors' hands now.
Please stay calm.

309
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:22,560
Both Mr. Phum
and Ms. Pakarang will be safe.

310
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:25,479
Okay.

311
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:28,440
But I hope that Pakarang dies.

312
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:33,200
Ms. Sairung, how can you say that?

313
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:00,600
How are they?

314
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:03,400
Ms. Pakarang is safe now.

315
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:05,800
And my father?

316
00:33:06,480 --> 00:33:10,720
The doctor is doing everything he can.
Please stay calm.

317
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:33,200
It'll be alright.

318
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:16,520
Please sit down first.

319
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:19,199
Will the doctor be able to save Dad?

320
00:34:21,679 --> 00:34:23,440
Everyone must be doing their best.

321
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:27,440
I want to do something to help him.

322
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:33,238
If you want to help him, I know one way.

323
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:35,280
I don't know if you'll believe it.

324
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:40,520
Tell me. I'll do anything.

325
00:34:57,680 --> 00:34:59,680
Two hundred joules. Clear.

326
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,480
What is Mr. Narathon doing?

327
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:39,240
Meditating and sending merit
to Mr. Phum's karmic creditors.

328
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,800
Superstitious nonsense.

329
00:37:03,040 --> 00:37:04,120
Let's go.

330
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,159
How is my father?

331
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:16,400
He's safe now.

332
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:20,319
Thank you so much, Doctor.

333
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:21,839
You should thank Mr. Phum too.

334
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:24,399
His heart stopped,

335
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:26,840
but he fought his way back.

336
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,920
It's unbelievable.

337
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:31,920
Excuse me.

338
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:04,520
Thank you, Dad,

339
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:06,320
for still fighting.

340
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:18,160
I know what I'm doing

341
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:21,240
makes me seem like a terrible son.

342
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:29,680
But...

343
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:36,720
I still have to seek justice for Sarai.

344
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:48,680
I'm sorry, Dad.

345
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,959
What terrible misfortune.

346
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:18,480
But it's lucky that both of them are safe.

347
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:22,840
Yes. But Mr. Phum is still in the ICU.

348
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:24,759
They'll monitor him for another night.

349
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:28,760
If nothing happens, he should be
moved to a private room tomorrow.

350
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:34,999
Dear, we should visit Mr. Phum.

351
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:38,840
When you were sick,
he helped coordinate everything for us.

352
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:41,360
I know.

353
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,400
Narathon must have been very shocked.

354
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:48,399
Yes.

355
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:51,239
This incident made me realize

356
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:54,200
that Mr. Narathon actually
loves Mr. Phum very much.

357
00:39:56,400 --> 00:40:00,440
Mr. Phum loves Mr. Narathon just as much.

358
00:40:04,680 --> 00:40:05,999
How do you know that, Na?

359
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,840
When we went to save you on Skull Island.

360
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,199
I could tell from Mr. Phum's expression

361
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:13,000
how much he loved Mr. Narathon.

362
00:40:14,160 --> 00:40:17,360
Even though sometimes
they seem like they don't get along.

363
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:20,840
That's how people are.

364
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:26,760
When we see someone every day,
we don't realize we love them.

365
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:30,920
But when we're about to lose them,
that's when we finally feel it.

366
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,920
Sometimes it may already be too late.

367
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:21,080
Mom,

368
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:25,320
where are you? I miss you so much.

369
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,240
Auntie.

370
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:17,400
Why are you standing here
in the dark, Auntie?

371
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,800
You can see me?

372
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:24,280
Yes.

373
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:32,000
Why are you crying?

374
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:34,920
I miss my mom.

375
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:40,600
Where is your mom?

376
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:45,640
I don't know. I've never met her.

377
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:50,479
Some people say she doesn't love me.

378
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:51,760
That's why she left me.

379
00:42:56,680 --> 00:43:00,000
That's not true.
All mothers love their children.

380
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:03,840
Really?

381
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,000
Yes.

382
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:13,360
She must be busy with work.

383
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:18,440
But why has she never come to see me?

384
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:20,840
I miss her.

385
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:23,280
I want to see her.

386
00:43:23,800 --> 00:43:25,760
I miss my mom.

387
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:28,040
I want to see my mom.

388
00:43:29,080 --> 00:43:31,960
I miss my mom. I want to see her.

389
00:43:32,920 --> 00:43:36,400
I miss my mom.

390
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:39,079
I want to see my mom.

391
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:42,720
I miss my mom. I want to see my mom.

392
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:45,160
I miss my mom.

393
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:48,200
I miss my mom.

394
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:50,960
I want to see my mom.

395
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:53,760
I want to see my mom.

396
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:56,520
I miss my mom.

397
00:43:57,200 --> 00:43:58,840
I miss my mom.

398
00:43:59,360 --> 00:44:00,960
I miss my mom.

399
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:02,880
I want to see my mom.

400
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:17,840
I've put up with you long enough.

401
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:25,119
Sarai?

402
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:26,560
You must pay for what you did.

403
00:44:32,160 --> 00:44:35,000
Let me go. I'm begging you!

404
00:44:36,720 --> 00:44:38,559
Can you help me contact Sarai?

405
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:40,320
I have something
I want to talk to her about.

406
00:45:09,920 --> 00:45:12,160
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
